Sinopse: The Spanish Victoria has been living in Berlin for three months and working in a coffee shop. She goes to a night club to drink and dance and when she is leaving the place, she meets the German troublemakers Sonne, Boxer, Blinker and Fuß. Sonne flirts with her and they go to the roof deck of a building to drink and talk. Soon she needs to leave because it is late night and she has to work on the next morning, and Sonne goes with her to her work to drink a cold chocolate. Out of the blue, his friends arrive and tell to Sonne that they need to pay the debt for protection of Boxer when he was in the prison. The protector is requiring them for a four-man-job, but Fuß is completely drugged and can not go. Now Victoria is called by Sonne and his friends to help them in a dangerous night driving a stolen getaway car.—Claudio Carvalho, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil
